title: 'It never stops, does it?' Reckless Valour on stage again
text:
Topix › Pacific Travel › 'It never stops, does it?' Reckless V... 'It never stops, does it?' Reckless Valour on stage again 3 hrs ago Read more: Canberra City News 
CANBERRA contemporary youth dance ensemble Quantum Leap, QL2, is about to stage a reinterpretation of a production first performed in 2005 and remounted for the Adelaide Arts Festival in 2007. The original choreographers of "Reckless Valour," Fiona Malone, Rowan Marchingo, Natalie Cursio and Jodie Farrugia have returned to town to redevelop the work, originally created in association with the Australian War Memorial. Start the conversation, or Read more at Canberra City News.
